<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="817" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d817">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 741.8215/48.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-09">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 9, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>British Government objects to G. Mason, alleging incompetency.
                            [Appointment on the boundary commission.] Appointment another surveyor
                            imperative. Boundary Commission ready to proceed. Expense delay
                            chargeable to the Liberian Government. Liberian President requests me to
                            ascertain whether Captain Young may serve as Liberian Commissioner.
                            Believe British Government would appreciate such service.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Crum.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>